@page "/"

<PageTitle>SSR Compatibility Test - BlazorBlueprint</PageTitle>

<div class="max-w-4xl space-y-8">
    <div class="space-y-3">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">SSR Compatibility Test</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-muted-foreground">
            This demo runs with <strong>no render mode</strong> on the root Routes component.
            Every page renders as static HTML on the server — no SignalR, no WebAssembly, no JS interop.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-lg border bg-card p-6 space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">How this works</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground list-disc list-inside">
            <li>In the other demos, <code class="text-xs bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">@@rendermode="InteractiveServer"</code> is set on <code class="text-xs bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">&lt;Routes&gt;</code> in App.razor — making the entire app interactive.</li>
            <li>In this demo, <code class="text-xs bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">&lt;Routes&gt;</code> has <strong>no render mode</strong>. Components render as pure static HTML.</li>
            <li><code class="text-xs bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">OnAfterRenderAsync</code> never runs. JS interop is unavailable. <code class="text-xs bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">ElementReference</code> values are empty.</li>
            <li>Click handlers, two-way binding, and event callbacks don't work — the page is plain HTML.</li>
            <li>Forms work only via traditional HTTP POST with the <code class="text-xs bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">Name</code> parameter and <code class="text-xs bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">&lt;EditForm&gt;</code> with <code class="text-xs bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">FormName</code>.</li>
            <li>The <a href="/interactive-island" class="underline text-foreground">Interactive Island</a> page shows how to opt individual components into interactivity.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <a href="/static-components" class="group rounded-lg border p-6 hover:border-foreground/25 transition-colors">
            <h3 class="font-semibold group-hover:underline">Static Components</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mt-1">
                Components that render correctly as pure static HTML.
            </p>
        </a>

        <a href="/form-components" class="group rounded-lg border p-6 hover:border-foreground/25 transition-colors">
            <h3 class="font-semibold group-hover:underline">Form Components</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mt-1">
                Form inputs tested with SSR form postback.
            </p>
        </a>

        <a href="/interactive-components" class="group rounded-lg border p-6 hover:border-foreground/25 transition-colors">
            <h3 class="font-semibold group-hover:underline">Needs Interactivity</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mt-1">
                Components that render HTML but lose all interactive behavior.
            </p>
        </a>

        <a href="/js-dependent" class="group rounded-lg border p-6 hover:border-foreground/25 transition-colors">
            <h3 class="font-semibold group-hover:underline">JS Dependent</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mt-1">
                Components that are non-functional or broken without JS interop.
            </p>
        </a>

        <a href="/interactive-island" class="group rounded-lg border p-6 hover:border-foreground/25 transition-colors md:col-span-2">
            <h3 class="font-semibold group-hover:underline">Interactive Island Demo</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mt-1">
                Shows how to opt individual components into @@rendermode="InteractiveServer" while the rest of the page stays static.
            </p>
        </a>
    </div>
</div>
